data.name: textBox5.Text
data.value: Variables are pieces of data which keep track of the state of your game. A project contains several variables by default. If you need more, you can add your own using the interface on the right. Variables are limited to values between 0 and 255.

data.name: textBox2.Text
data.value: Events are run after each user command is processed. They can be used to do things things like add 1 to the player's health, or to consume fuel or batteries for objects that are on. They can also be used to create randomly occuring events such as the thief in Zork. Rules have a name to identify them and code to execute.

data.name: textBox12.Text
data.value: The walkthrough is the complete set of commands used to test your game from start to finish. By storing it here you can have it readily available for pasting into the test window. This will also help the teacher play (and grade) your project.
